    "description": "Nerpa is a agent for linking biosynthetic gene clusters (BGCs) to known nonribosomal peptides (NRPs). BGCs are predicted in genome sequences (FASTA or GBK) with antiSMASH. Known NRPs are accepted in the SMILES format and processed with rBAN.",
